# MCP toolchain

When the **nwn-project** MCP server is connected, prefer typed tool calls over manual shell:

| Task | MCP tool |
|------|----------|
| Layout check | `nwn.project.validate_layout` |
| Build | `nwn.nasher.build` |
| Compile | `nwn.script.compile_all`, `nwn.script.diagnostics` |
| Symbol search | `nwn.script.find_symbol` |
| Resref lookup | `nwn.nasher.resource_lookup` |
| Git diff | `nwn.project.diff_summary` |
| ADR | `nwn.docs.add_decision` |

Fall back to `tools/*.sh` or `scripts/*.ps1` when MCP is unavailable.

## Permissions (nwn-mcp.config.json)

- `allowDeleteFiles: false` — blocks `nwn.nasher.clean` by default
- `allowAuroraLaunch: false` — blocks Aurora launch by default
- `allowStartServer: false` — blocks NWNX server start by default

Do not enable dangerous permissions without explicit user request.

